00:02:36.270 --> 00:02:37.860 align:middle line:90%
this concept of loneliness?

00:02:37.860 --> 00:02:42.480 align:middle line:84%
Because it's my hunch that it's
really manifesting for people

00:02:42.480 --> 00:02:46.080 align:middle line:84%
actually in very different ways
that maybe we don't normally

00:02:46.080 --> 00:02:48.270 align:middle line:84%
think of as being
lonely, which is

00:02:48.270 --> 00:02:50.070 align:middle line:90%
why it's becoming so pervasive.

00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:50.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:02:50.950 --> 00:02:53.310 align:middle line:84%
Well, and I think that something
that you're pointing to here--

00:02:53.310 --> 00:02:54.768 align:middle line:84%
and that's really,
really important

00:02:54.768 --> 00:02:59.190 align:middle line:84%
to know-- is that there can
be somebody that is surrounded

00:02:59.190 --> 00:03:04.030 align:middle line:84%
by a lot of people, or maybe
by a family, or what have you.

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:08.100 align:middle line:84%
